Title: Boundary One-Point Functions, Scattering, and Background Vacuum
  Solutions in Toda Theories
Authors: V.A. Fateev (1 and 2), E. Onofri (1 and 3) ((1) Laboratoire de
  Physique Mathematique, Universite' Montpellier II, Pl. E.Bataillon,
  Montpellier, France, (2) Landau Institute for Theoretical Physics,
  ul.Kosygina 2, Moscow, Russia, (3) Dipartimento di Fisica, Universita' di
  Parma e I.N.F.N., Gruppo Collegato di Parma, Parma, Italy)
Comments: 20 pages, LaTeX
Report-no: LPM/02-11, UPRF-2002-11
\\
  The parametric families of integrable boundary affine Toda theories are
considered. We calculate boundary one-point functions and propose boundary
S-matrices in these theories. We use boundary one-point functions and S-matrix
amplitudes to derive boundary ground state energies and exact solutions
describing classical vacuum configurations.
